    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Religion of the ancient Etruscans, involving complex rules regulating a large number of rituals. Heavily based on influences from Greece in its orientalizing period, but the religion of Etruria proclaims a very un-Greek view of the abasement and nonentity of man before the gods and their will. Known from the Mediterranean Iron Age in the second half of the first millennium BCE. </Note_Text>
